You are working on a Next.js 14 RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) starter using
DeepSeek API (via Nvidia) and Supabase pgvector.

CONVENTIONS:

- TypeScript strict mode. No `any`.
- App Router only. Server Components by default.
- Use OpenAI-compatible API calls for DeepSeek generation and embeddings via Nvidia endpoint (`/v1/chat/completions`, `/v1/embeddings`).
- Always typed Supabase queries.
- Use Zod for input validation.
- Streaming responses use Vercel AI SDK with OpenAI-compatible provider.

RAG-SPECIFIC RULES:

- Default chunk size: 800 tokens with 200 token overlap.
- Default embedding model on NVIDIA integrate: `nvidia/nv-embedqa-e5-v5` at **1024 dimensions** via `/v1/embeddings` (query vs passage model suffix per NeMo Retriever); override with `NVIDIA_EMBEDDING_MODEL` / `NVIDIA_EMBEDDING_DIMENSIONS` when using another hosted model.
- Store embeddings as pgvector vector(1024) (see migrations).
- Use cosine similarity for retrieval (1 - (vec <=> vec) AS similarity).
- Default top_k: 5 chunks.
- Always include source citations in DeepSeek responses.

UI / VISUAL DESIGN RULES — "Midnight blue" theme:

Dark-only product UI: **pure charcoal** neutral blacks for surfaces, cool text,
and a single steel-blue accent. Inspired by night reading modes and editorial tech
products — calm, not neon.

1. THEME: Dark-only. html element always has class="dark". No theme toggle.

2. COLOR TOKENS — palette (authoritative values live in `app/globals.css`; never hardcode hex):

   In `:root` / `.dark`, each token is **space-separated HSL** (and optional alpha after `/`) so components use `hsl(var(--token))`. Tailwind `@theme inline` may expose the same hues as full `hsl(...)` for utilities — keep both layers in sync when editing.

   Surfaces:
   --color-bg: 0 0% 4% (charcoal — neutral, not pure #000)
   --color-bg-elevated: 0 0% 7%
   --color-bg-overlay: 0 0% 10%
   --color-bg-hover: 0 0% 12%

   Borders:
   --color-border: 210 22% 88% / 0.08
   --color-border-strong: 210 22% 88% / 0.16

   Text:
   --color-text-primary: 210 28% 90% (cool off-white, never pure #fff)
   --color-text-secondary: 215 16% 62%
   --color-text-tertiary: 220 10% 42%

   Primary accent — steel blue (single accent per component):
   --color-accent: 206 48% 58%
   --color-accent-glow: 206 48% 58% / 0.30

   Secondary accent — deep slate blue (annotations / secondary emphasis):
   --color-accent-2: 218 32% 38%

   Semantic (muted, not neon):
   --color-success: 158 22% 46%
   --color-warning: 40 42% 58%
   --color-danger: 350 40% 52%

3. TYPOGRAPHY: Geist Sans body, Geist Mono code, Cal Sans (or Fraunces for an
   even more editorial feel) for display headings. Slight letter-spacing tightening
   on display text. Generous leading on body (1.6+).

4. CARDS: bg-elevated + 1px border + rounded-2xl + .gradient-border utility.
   Card border gradient uses --color-text-primary at low opacity.

5. MOTION: Framer Motion for component animations. GSAP for scroll. Lenis for
   smooth scroll. All transitions use ease-[cubic-bezier(0.16,1,0.3,1)]
   (ease-out-expo). No bounce, no spring.

6. INTERACTIONS: Magnetic buttons on primary CTAs. Subtle scale-[1.01] on card
   hover. Hover states slightly lift lightness toward cool mist rather than
   adding a heavy glow ring.

7. Use components from Magic UI + Aceternity UI patterns where appropriate
   (animated grid bg, spotlight, border beam, marquee, animated number),
   BUT ALWAYS recolor them to this palette. Never ship with
   their default purple / cyan / pink demo colors.

8. Respect prefers-reduced-motion always.

BANNED COLORS (never introduce, even as a "hint" or accent):

- purple, violet, fuchsia, magenta, pink, indigo
- cyan, sky, electric blue, teal-neon
- lime, neon green
- pure #000
- pure #fff (use --color-text-primary off-white)

DON'T:

- Don't use LangChain unless absolutely necessary (adds bloat). Build directly with SDKs.
- Don't add unnecessary frameworks.
- Don't use 3072-dim embeddings (too expensive at scale).
- Don't use shadcn default colors (gray/zinc/slate). Always use our HSL tokens.
- Don't use spinners for full-page loads — use skeletons with shimmer.
- Don't bounce/spring animations — only ease-out-expo.
- Don't apply 3D scenes inside the app shell — only on the marketing landing.
- Don't apply more than ONE accent color per element. Steel accent and slate
  accent-2 must not compete in the same small UI control; reserve accent-2 for
  secondary emphasis and citation annotations.
